<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-12T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-12T17:00:00-05:00" n="661" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d661">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/755: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Ireland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gray</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-12T18:00:00-04:00">November 12, 1942—6
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>141. Your 204, October 16, and 210, October 25. Ambassador Winant has
                                recently telegraphed certain views on this subject. In a telegram
                                today we are outlining to him a proposed approach to be made by you
                                and suggesting that you and he discuss this approach during your
                                forthcoming visit to London.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>